author: kfogel
msg: Fix issue #1195: 'svn ci -N' could fail to commit named files.
This is my 1000th commit to the Subversion repository.  Champagne will
be served in the main ballroom, followed by dinner and a dance.
* subversion/include/svn_path.h
(svn_path_condense_targets): Add new `remove_redundancies' flag.
Also, rewrite documentation in active voice.
* subversion/libsvn_subr/target.c
(svn_path_condense_targets): Take new `remove_redundancies' flag.
All callers changed to pass true, except for svn_client_commit.
* subversion/libsvn_client/commit.c
(svn_client_commit): In the nonrecursive case, pass false for the
new remove_redundancies flag to svn_path_condense_targets,
otherwise pass true.  Also, check for URLs among targets.
* subversion/libsvn_client/commit_util.c
(look_up_committable): New helper function.
(harvest_committables): Use look_up_committable as an early out
option, to avoid getting duplicate items in the commit list.
(svn_client__harvest_committables): Use look_up_committable to
check whether unversioned parents of commit items are also in the
commit list.
* subversion/tests/clients/cmdline/commit_tests.py
(commit_in_dir_scheduled_for_addition): Tweak to expect new error.
(commit_nonrecursive): Tweak to expect the right output.
(test_list): Expect commit_nonrecursive to pass now.
